Common.LongDescription.Common.Text:
CBRE, Inc. is pleased to exclusively offer Seventy-One Eleven Building for purchase. The property consists of approximately 11,886 sq. ft. office building on 0.58 Acres
of land in Riverside, California within Riverside County. The property is situated in the corner of Indiana Avenue and Washington Street, with excellent freeway visibility
and access, approximately 20 miles from Ontario International Airport and 60 miles east of Los Angeles. The new owner of this highly attractive and beautifully landscaped and stabilized property will benefit from high tenant retention and low future capital expenditures.

Common.Strapline.Common.Text: 11,886 SF Office Building -  Investment or Owner User Sale

Common.SpaceDescription.Common.Text:
Suite 101 & 102 are leased as one unit to an allergy and asthma specialty practice. This medical suite was converted from
general office in 2016 and features new modern finishes, a large patient lobby, six (6) exam rooms, private restroom, large break room, lab, data room, physician office and specialized 'shot room". This suite covers the north end of the building with window-line on the north, east and west sides allowing for great views and ample natural light.

Suite 103 is located on the Haven corridor side of the building off the elevator lobby and
features floor-to-ceiling glass entryway. Refurbished in 2016, this suite has five (5) private offices, lobby and an open work space. Established tenant since 2011, with history of renewal, this general office user has synergistic relationships with other general office users in the building, however, there is "upside potential" to convert to medical in the future.

Suite 108:
An established insurance agency occupies this highly visible office suite that is off the building lobby. Floor to ceiling glass with double-door entry leads to reception area, open work area concept and two (2) private offices. The upgraded modern finishes are enhanced by the floor-to-ceiling glass that runs the length of the suite providing abundant natural lighting and premium views of the beautiful front landscaping and gardens. Synergistic mix of real estate related businesses provides motivation for long-term tenancy by existing tenant, however, future owner has potential of converting the suite to medical use. Would be ideal location for pharmacy, ophthalmology, orthodontics, dentist, primary care or medical specialty practice.

Suite 120:
Busy escrow office occupies Suite 120, a beautiful end-cap suite. 2020. Office Improvements were completed in 2012 and feature a direct entry off parking lot, reception area, conference room, two (2) private restrooms, break room, six (6) private offices, open area and two (2) large offices. With glass s line on 3 sides, this suite enjoys excellent natural lighting and views of the lush landscaping that fronts the Building. Potential for medical conversion makes this an attractive investment as medical users prefer direct entry and interior restrooms. A secondary entrance would appeal to a physician that desires a private entrance. Imaging, primary care, urgent care and orthodontics would be attracted to the suite's size and location in the building.

Suite 220:
An ideal small suite for a small general office business such as insurance, financial advisor or home health care. Future conversion to medical would make it attractive to single physician medical practice, endodontist or psychiatry/psychology practice. Gleaming wood floor enhance to open work concept that features one (1) private office). Easy access to plumbing allows for installation of wet bar/kitchenettes and/or exam sinks in the future.

Suite 225/230
Leased to an established primary care practice that specializes in diabetes care and prevention. This beautiful medical space has everything a practice could need from exam rooms to the the corner physician office with a view. All of the interior finishes were updated when the suite was converted to medical in 2014 and reflect a modern, high-end medical practice. The lobby features tile floor, decorative soffit and lighting and a built-in reception desk with solid-surface counter-top. The physician office is located in the southeast corner of the suite provided spectacular views and abundant natural lighting. Leased while the market was still in recovery mode this suite has future upside leasing potential in a growing medical market.

Common.LocationDescription.Common.Text:
Perfectly situated near the neighborhoods of Atwater
Village, Glassell Park, Los Feliz, Silverlake, Highland Park and

investors.

Common.LongDescription.Common.Text:
This City of Glendale owner/user or investment opportunity
is adjacent to Atwater Village on one side and Glassell Park
on the other. 3608 San Fernando Rd was tastefully
converted from an industrial warehouse property into
modern creative offices in 2013/2014. A second floor was
also added at that time, along with secured interior parking
featuring high bow-truss ceiling. The finishing touch of a
new loft area was completed within the building in 2019.
The interior is comprised of exposed sandblasted red brick
and wood beam ceilings, offering a trendy and cool
ambiance. One unit is currently owner-occupied and will
be delivered vacant. The other unit (3610) is currently
rented providing Buyer with excellent current income to
lower their operating expense.
